---
import ArticleLayout from "../../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Leather Care Mistakes to Avoid | Expert Tips | Empire Cleaning Group";
const heading = "Leather Care Mistakes to Avoid";
const description =
  "Everyday products can damage leather finish. Use a safer cleaning and conditioning routine.";
---

<ArticleLayout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={description}
  heading={heading}
  backHref="/en/conseils"
  backLabel="← Back to expert tips"
>
  <div class="article-meta" style="margin-bottom: 2rem; color: #666; font-style: italic;">
    <span>Category: Maintenance</span> | <span>Updated: December 08, 2024</span>
  </div>

  <p class="lead" style="font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--color-primary); font-weight: 500;">
    Leather needs proper cleaning and conditioning. Incorrect products can accelerate wear and damage surface finish.
  </p>

  <h2>Avoid baby wipes and harsh household products</h2>
  <p>
    Many products contain chemicals that are not designed for leather and can weaken protective coating over time.
  </p>

  <h2>Avoid oily DIY treatments</h2>
  <p>Heavy oils can leave residue, attract dirt, and alter leather appearance.</p>

  <h2>A safer maintenance process</h2>

  <div
    style="background-color: #f8f9fa; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent); padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; border-radius: 4px;"
  >
    <ol style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.25rem;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.65rem;">
        <strong>Dust weekly:</strong> Use a soft dry cloth.
      </li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.65rem;">
        <strong>Clean gently:</strong> Use a damp cloth for minor marks.
      </li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0;">
        <strong>Condition periodically:</strong> Apply professional leather conditioner after proper cleaning.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</ArticleLayout>
